      "grammarTip": "<h3>Wechselpräpositionen (Two-Way Prepositions)</h3><p>Some prepositions can take either the Dative or Accusative case. Use <strong>Dativ</strong> for a static location (answers 'Wo?' - Where?). Use <strong>Accusative</strong> for movement towards a place (answers 'Wohin?' - Where to?).</p><ul><li><strong>an (at/to):</strong> Ich warte <strong>am</strong> Flugsteig. (Dativ - I'm waiting *at* the gate). Ich gehe <strong>an den</strong> Flugsteig. (Accusative - I'm going *to* the gate).</li><li><strong>in (in/into):</strong> Mein Laptop ist <strong>im</strong> Handgepäck. (Dativ - My laptop is *in* the hand luggage). Ich packe meinen Laptop <strong>ins</strong> Handgepäck. (Accusative - I'm packing my laptop *into* the hand luggage).</li><li><strong>auf (on/onto):</strong> Das Gepäck liegt <strong>auf dem</strong> Band. (Dativ - The luggage is *on* the belt). Ich lege mein Gepäck <strong>auf das</strong> Band. (Accusative - I'm putting my luggage *onto* the belt).</li></ul>"
